WEBVTT

00:00.923 --> 00:02.924
Carroll was convicted in 2004

00:03.045 --> 00:05.293
for the murders
of 14 young women.

00:05.395 --> 00:07.927
The warden granted Joe
Carroll's request for a transfer.

00:08.034 --> 00:08.738
He's leaving.

00:08.834 --> 00:10.185
Joe's not in the
transport vehicle.

00:10.299 --> 00:11.312
Where the hell is he?

00:13.134 --> 00:15.211
So Joe's free,
and now I get locked up.

00:15.323 --> 00:17.172
Protective custody.
Better if I don't know.

00:17.356 --> 00:18.623
Quantico sent in a new guy.

00:18.721 --> 00:20.629
Nick Donovan,
top of the food chain.

00:20.722 --> 00:23.032
This investigation starts
at my desk now.

00:23.139 --> 00:23.991
Joe Carroll!

00:24.454 --> 00:25.729
How the hell are you?

00:26.113 --> 00:27.140
I'm Roderick.

00:27.271 --> 00:29.593
Emma, why did you leave us?

00:29.708 --> 00:30.858
Emma!

00:30.951 --> 00:32.455
Any word from Jacob and Paul?

00:32.555 --> 00:33.313
They haven't called.

00:33.438 --> 00:34.701
- Hang on. I'm gonna get us some help.
- Thank you.

00:35.398 --> 00:36.918
I love my wife.

00:37.022 --> 00:38.399
She's not here.

00:38.820 --> 00:41.026
Losing Claire was a mistake,

00:41.137 --> 00:42.692
but I have an idea
how we can find her.

00:42.817 --> 00:44.956
Agent Weston, tell
us where Claire is.

00:45.045 --> 00:45.930
I don't know anything.

00:46.027 --> 00:46.955
Claire's location.

00:47.052 --> 00:48.914
He's the only one who does
know where Claire is.

00:49.078 --> 00:50.124
Everyone's waiting.

00:50.234 --> 00:51.646
- What for?
- For you.

00:53.437 --> 00:56.413
Good morning, everybody.

00:57.067 --> 00:59.185
How did Carroll
escape in a helicopter

00:59.298 --> 01:00.264
in broad daylight?

01:00.375 --> 01:01.941
Carroll's people infiltrated
the prison system,

01:02.042 --> 01:03.137
the warden was compromised.

01:03.246 --> 01:06.067
Agent Parker how many people are
a part of Joe Carroll's cult?

01:06.239 --> 01:08.061
Early evidence suggested
somewhere under 12,

01:08.188 --> 01:11.219
but in light of Carroll's
recent escape,

01:11.338 --> 01:13.368
tactical resources, manpower,

01:13.517 --> 01:14.904
it could be upwards
of a hundred.

01:15.016 --> 01:16.232
How did you arrive
at that number?

01:16.344 --> 01:18.406
Carroll's visitors log
in prison contained

01:18.523 --> 01:20.188
47 false identities,

01:20.292 --> 01:22.863
and his internet usage,
although heavily encrypted,

01:22.972 --> 01:24.281
suggested twice that many.

01:24.398 --> 01:26.080
That's a guess at best, Agent.

01:26.183 --> 01:27.566
Are we looking
for a cult compound

01:27.704 --> 01:28.919
like Waco or Jonestown?

01:29.039 --> 01:30.373
Yes. We believe
there to be

01:30.494 --> 01:32.433
some sort of safe haven.

01:32.553 --> 01:34.086
But you don't know
where that is.

01:35.358 --> 01:37.721
No. We don't.

01:39.547 --> 01:41.388
Our working theory is that it's

01:41.511 --> 01:44.203
within a 3-state radius
of Virginia.

01:44.311 --> 01:45.239
Let me get this straight.

01:45.356 --> 01:46.586
There's an organized gathering

01:46.715 --> 01:48.346
of dozens of killers out there,

01:48.600 --> 01:50.486
and you have no idea
where they are.

01:50.591 --> 01:51.783
Can I just remind everyone

01:51.930 --> 01:54.901
that this is a briefing
and not an inquisition?

01:55.019 --> 01:56.145
Who are these people
he recruits?

01:56.248 --> 01:57.566
They can't all be
serial killers.

01:57.677 --> 01:59.537
He has recruited from
all walks of life--

01:59.660 --> 02:03.849
housewives, teachers, accountants,
military, law enforcement.

02:03.969 --> 02:05.295
All of whom fit
the personality types

02:05.408 --> 02:07.151
associated with
cult susceptibility--

02:07.267 --> 02:09.954
empty, lost, maladjusted.

02:10.061 --> 02:11.050
They're full-blow
psychopaths.

02:11.152 --> 02:13.190
The acolytes that we've
encountered have run the gamut

02:13.343 --> 02:15.113
from visionary to hedonistic,

02:15.242 --> 02:17.398
one-time killers,
mission-oriented killers,

02:17.528 --> 02:19.023
fans of killers, groupies.

02:19.136 --> 02:22.372
Mr. Hardy, an agent was captured
and assaulted by cult members.

02:22.487 --> 02:24.187
Was he able to identify
his captors?

02:24.293 --> 02:25.693
That agent--
Mike Weston--

02:25.839 --> 02:27.450
we have a sketch artist
standing by

02:27.573 --> 02:29.138
for the moment he
regains consciousness.

02:29.256 --> 02:30.491
And his cult--
have you identified

02:30.617 --> 02:32.322
their religion or manifesto?

02:32.433 --> 02:35.287
Both a novelist
and a professor,

02:35.430 --> 02:37.650
Carroll's using
literary themes found

02:37.781 --> 02:39.615
in the works
of Gothic Romanticism.

02:39.727 --> 02:42.457
"All that we see or seem

02:43.169 --> 02:46.820
is but a dream
within a dream."

02:47.387 --> 02:50.642
That is what
this moment is for me.

02:50.750 --> 02:52.709
He's speaking to his subjects

02:52.829 --> 02:56.142
with the promise of
elevating their lives--

02:56.783 --> 02:59.164
through death, one
experiences life.

02:59.278 --> 03:05.104
I will never forget
what you have all done for me,

03:05.343 --> 03:07.894
the sacrifices you have made,

03:08.599 --> 03:11.982
but now the time
has come for you...

03:12.102 --> 03:14.775
By his own admission,
Carroll has engaged his followers

03:14.911 --> 03:16.510
to write their own chapters,

03:16.624 --> 03:20.037
become part of this
novel that he's writing.

03:20.166 --> 03:25.033
I want to hear from each
and every one of you.

03:25.154 --> 03:26.742
Tell me...

03:26.886 --> 03:29.849
what inspires you.

03:29.978 --> 03:31.559
I need your help

03:32.418 --> 03:36.688
to finish our story.

03:36.801 --> 03:38.032
He's united with his people.

03:38.135 --> 03:40.794
He will do something
to ignite them to action.

03:40.952 --> 03:42.235
I see it in your eyes.

03:42.351 --> 03:44.705
I know you are ready.

03:46.779 --> 03:49.394
It's time for him to tell
the next part of his story.

03:51.770 --> 03:53.585
And so we begin.

03:57.058 --> 03:59.317
